        "content": "<p>The theorem <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=Finset.induction#doc\">docs#Finset.induction</a> and its cousin <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=Finset.induction_on#doc\">docs#Finset.induction_on</a> both have a hypothesis <code>(insert : âˆ€ â¦ƒa : Î±â¦„ {s : Finset Î±}, a âˆ‰ s â†’ motive s â†’ motive (insert a s))</code>. Why are <code>a</code> and <code>s</code> implicit here?</p>",
        "id": 515370896,
        "sender_full_name": "Aaron Liu",
        "timestamp": 1746037185
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>One small advantage that gives, is that in the proof of <code>Finset.induction</code> you can write <code>insert ha</code> instead of <code>insert a s ha</code>. It also affects the patterns when doing </p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">induction</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">t</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kn\">using</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Finset</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">induction</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">with</span>\n<span class=\"bp\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">insert</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ha</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">...</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>which may or may not be a good thing.</p>\n<p>Side note: <code>a</code> is <em>strict</em> implicit, which allows the proof of <code>Finset.induction_on</code> to be <code>Finset.induction empty insert s</code> instead of <code>Finset.induction empty @insert s</code>.</p>",
        "id": 515375360,
        "sender_full_name": "Floris van Doorn",
        "timestamp": 1746038696
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"111080\">Floris van Doorn</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/287929-mathlib4/topic/.60Finset.2Einduction.60.20implicitness/near/515375360\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>One small advantage that gives, is that in the proof of <code>Finset.induction</code> you can write <code>insert ha</code> instead of <code>insert a s ha</code>.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>This is four characters, compared to all the time I've spent doing</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">induction</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">t</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kn\">using</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Finset</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">induction</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">with</span>\n<span class=\"bp\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">empty</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">...</span>\n<span class=\"bp\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">@</span><span class=\"n\">insert</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">s</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ha</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">...</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>that I questioned why it was implicit in the first place.</p>",
        "id": 515376012,
        "sender_full_name": "Aaron Liu",
        "timestamp": 1746038938
    },
